        <h1 style="font-size:24px; color:brown">Career & Employment Service</h1>
        <h2 style="color:blue"><b>UOE CareerHub</b> is an online jobs board for JCU students. Access CareerHub with your JCU username and password to search for employment. Employers and individuals can advertise job vacancies to students at no cost!</h2>
        <h2 style="color:blue">CareerHub for UOE students also has information on: </h2>        
        <ul style="color:blue">
            <li><h3>Upcoming career events</h3></li>
            <li><h3>Workshops</h3></li>
            <li><h3>Appointments (Job application check, Career Planning/Counselling)</h3></li>
            <li><h3>Career resources &#8211; templates/fact sheets</h3></li>
            <li><h3>Web links</h3></li>
        </ul>

        <h2 style="color:blue"><b>Supporting Students</b> &#8211; we provide career planning/counselling appointments, job search support including job application appointments, job vacancies advertised on CareerHub, workshops/employer information sessions/events (all advertised on CareerHub).</h2>
        <h2 style="color:blue"><b>Supporting Employers</b> &#8211; we provide many opportunities for employers to connect with JCU students and alumni. Some of these include; free job vacancy advertising on CareerHub, targeted eMailouts, and on campus information sessions and events including the annual Careers Fair. </h2>
        <h2 style="color:blue"><b>Supporting Staff</b> &#8211; we can assist staff with in-lecture careers workshops including the LearnJCU CareerSmart program and job application workshops.</h2>
